+### Per-tick semantics
+
+The tick handler runs the per-fire sequence in a fixed order: resolve
+the active scheduler → re-read + validate `reckoner.schedulerConfig`
+→ query held petitions (writs in `new` phase carrying `ext.reckoner`)
+→ apply source / disabled gates inline (each failing writ produces a
+decline row + transition before the scheduler ever sees the candidate
+set) → dedupe surviving candidates against
+`(writId, writUpdatedAt)` → build one `SchedulerInput { candidates,
+capacity, now, config }` for the whole batch → call `evaluate` →
+apply each decision → append one Reckonings row per writ considered.
+
 ### Failure modes
 
 | Condition                                                          | Behavior |
 |---|---|
-| CDC event arrives before `phase:started`                           | Silently skipped; the catch-up scan reprocesses the writ post-seal. |
-| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | No `evaluate` call, no row, no transition. |
-| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix; evaluation is skipped (no row, no transition). |
-| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; evaluation skipped. |
-| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue. |
-| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire evaluation is skipped (no decision is applied). |
-| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; the decision is ignored. |
+| Tick fires before `phase:started` resolved the active scheduler    | The relay handler throws fail-loud `[reckoner] tick: activeScheduler not resolved …`. Production never trips this; tests use the throw to assert the pre-seal contract. |
+| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | The candidate is filtered out before `evaluate` is called; no row, no transition. |
+| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] tick: scheduler …` prefix; the entire tick is skipped (no rows, no transitions). |
+| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped. |
+| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; the stranger decision is ignored, in-scope decisions still apply. |
+| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped (no decision is applied for any writ). |
+| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; that single decision is ignored, sibling in-scope decisions still apply. |
 
